At 02:34 PM 1/26/2003, Gary Watts wrote:
>I want more electrical power.  Are there any recommended alternators out
>there that put out more juice?  What I'm looking for is something that puts
>out enough power to allow me to have a staff member running their laptop and
>a video camera off the 12v of the van while I'm on the road, without
>sacrificing having the van batteries getting a full charge.
>Should I install a second alternator in my 77 for this?

Probably not necessary.  Your stock alternator should have enough excess capacity to run a laptop and video camera (I'm estimating 5-10 amps total if run directly from DC) and still charge the battery, as long as you don't do most of your driving in dark rainstorms.

-David
